1
00:01:03,447 --> 00:01:05,381
<font color="#D900D9">(CAR HORNS HONKING)</font>

2
00:01:24,969 --> 00:01:28,871
- You have a loan app? Wonderful.
- Yeah. Terrific.

3
00:01:37,448 --> 00:01:42,715
My wife and I were having dinner
the other night... recently married.

4
00:01:42,786 --> 00:01:44,720
<font color="#D900D9">(CONTINUES, INDISTINCT)</font>

5
00:01:50,461 --> 00:01:53,123
- How can I help you, sir?
- Loretta,

6
00:01:53,197 --> 00:01:57,930
see the man talking
to your bank manager has his case open?

7
00:01:58,002 --> 00:02:00,527
Oh, that's Mr. Gwendon,
one of our assistant managers.

8
00:02:00,604 --> 00:02:02,697
Our manager is Mr. Schoen,
but he's not in today.

9
00:02:02,773 --> 00:02:05,674
- But you see the man with the briefcase.
- Yes.

10
00:02:05,743 --> 00:02:08,041
That's my partner.
He has a gun in there.

11
00:02:08,112 --> 00:02:11,707
If you don't do exactly what I tell you or
if you give me any kind of problem at all,

12
00:02:11,782 --> 00:02:13,844
I'm going to look at my
partner and he's going

13
00:02:13,869 --> 00:02:15,799
to shoot your Mr. Gwendon
between the eyes.

14
00:02:19,690 --> 00:02:22,158
<font color="#D900D9">(WHISPERS)</font>
Okay.

15
00:02:22,226 --> 00:02:25,133
All right, take one of those
big envelopes and put

16
00:02:25,158 --> 00:02:27,779
as many 100s, 50s and
20s as you can into it.

17
00:02:27,831 --> 00:02:29,960
Nothing with bank straps
or rubber bands.

18
00:02:29,985 --> 00:02:32,258
I don't want dye packs.
I don't want bait money.

19
00:02:32,302 --> 00:02:35,829
Start with the second drawer, and then the
one over there, under the money counter.

20
00:02:38,809 --> 00:02:43,212
Okay. It's okay. Come on, Loretta.
Key's right next to you.

21
00:02:43,280 --> 00:02:45,214
There you go.

22
00:02:50,521 --> 00:02:53,422
No bills off the bottom
of the drawer, please.

23
00:02:59,963 --> 00:03:02,488
This your first time
being robbed?

24
00:03:02,566 --> 00:03:06,502
You're doing great. Just smile so you
don't look like you're being held up.

25
00:03:08,005 --> 00:03:10,269
You got a very pretty smile.

26
00:03:10,340 --> 00:03:12,808
You got 20s? Give me the 20s.
I'll take those.

27
00:03:12,876 --> 00:03:14,810
There you go.
I'll put those in my pocket.

28
00:03:15,979 --> 00:03:17,913
There you go.

29
00:03:19,850 --> 00:03:22,512
I have to give my partner a sign.
Now, that's good.

30
00:03:22,586 --> 00:03:24,616
He's gonna wait until I'm
out of the building,

31
00:03:24,641 --> 00:03:26,410
make sure you haven't
set off the alarm.

32
00:03:26,457 --> 00:03:30,860
If you have, he's gonna shoot your
Mr. Gwendon between the eyes. Okay?

33
00:03:30,928 --> 00:03:34,659
- Okay.
- I think that'll do it, Loretta.

34
00:03:34,731 --> 00:03:37,359
Thank you.
Have a nice day.

35
00:03:37,434 --> 00:03:39,698
You too.

36
00:03:44,808 --> 00:03:48,869
Hey... she's cute, isn't she?

37
00:03:48,946 --> 00:03:50,880
Yeah, she seems very nice.

38
00:03:53,117 --> 00:03:55,051
Who was that?

39
00:04:22,045 --> 00:04:25,173
<font color="#D900D9">(IGNITION CRANKING)</font>

40
00:04:25,249 --> 00:04:27,308
<font color="#D900D9">(CONTINUES CRANKING)</font>

41
00:04:27,384 --> 00:04:29,978
No, no, no, no, no.

42
00:04:30,053 --> 00:04:33,887
<font color="#D900D9">(PUMPING GAS PEDAL)</font>
Son of a bitch!

43
00:04:33,957 --> 00:04:36,755
Fuck! Fuck!

44
00:04:36,827 --> 00:04:40,888
I think you flooded it.
Get out of the car, sir.

45
00:04:40,964 --> 00:04:45,094
- Hey, you wanna hear a funny story?
- Shut up and get out of the car!

46
00:04:45,169 --> 00:04:49,299
Yeah. Okay.

47
00:05:03,320 --> 00:05:05,254
<font color="#D900D9">(SHOUTING, CHATTER)</font>

48
00:05:14,965 --> 00:05:17,798
Go, go, go!

49
00:06:22,866 --> 00:06:25,596
You want somethin', Foley?

50
00:06:25,669 --> 00:06:29,503
Some fellas are goin' out of here.
What if I tell you where and when?

51
00:06:29,573 --> 00:06:30,240
How many?

52
00:06:30,265 --> 00:06:32,930
Expect you to look out for me,
let me run off work detail...

53
00:06:32,976 --> 00:06:35,376
Okay, okay.
How many goin' out?

54
00:06:35,445 --> 00:06:37,436
- I hear six.
- When?

55
00:06:37,514 --> 00:06:40,711
- Tonight.
- You know who they are?

56
00:06:40,784 --> 00:06:43,548
Yes, I do.
But I'm not gonna tell you just yet.

57
00:06:43,620 --> 00:06:46,714
Meet me in the chapel,
just before lockdown. Okay?

58
00:06:54,564 --> 00:06:56,498
- You all right?
- I love you, baby.

59
00:06:56,566 --> 00:06:59,399
Tonight's the big night.
You excited?

60
00:07:01,138 --> 00:07:05,268
- It's Super Bowl Sunday, okay?
- See you moved it up.

61
00:07:05,342 --> 00:07:08,436
- Why you think that?
- I saw you runnin' this mornin'.

62
00:07:08,512 --> 00:07:11,003
Stickin' to your routine
in case anybody happened to notice.

63
00:07:11,081 --> 00:07:14,573
But you only did a couple of miles,
instead of your usual five.

64
00:07:14,651 --> 00:07:18,781
Saving yourself for the big event. What
happened? Finish ahead of schedule?

65
00:07:18,855 --> 00:07:21,688
Mira, you see those posts out there?

66
00:07:21,758 --> 00:07:24,268
They're putting up another
fence 15 feet back

67
00:07:24,293 --> 00:07:26,583
the fence that's already
there, you know?

68
00:07:26,630 --> 00:07:30,031
So you figure, mira, we wait till Super
Bowl Sunday, they have that fence built...

69
00:07:30,100 --> 00:07:33,194
then, cono, we gotta dig what,
another nine, ten days, baby?

70
00:07:33,270 --> 00:07:35,204
- Yeah.
- I don't think so.

71
00:07:35,272 --> 00:07:38,879
So tonight, when it gets dark,
batta-bing, I'm outta here.

72
00:07:38,904 --> 00:07:40,859
Come on, Foley. You could come.

73
00:07:40,911 --> 00:07:44,540
I appreciate the offer,
and it's tempting.

74
00:07:44,614 --> 00:07:47,412
It's a long run to civilization.
What's it? A hundred miles to Miami?

75
00:07:47,484 --> 00:07:50,851
I'm too old to be tryin'
a stunt like that.

76
00:07:50,921 --> 00:07:53,651
So, you send me a postcard
when you get out.

77
00:07:56,226 --> 00:07:59,457
<font color="#D900D9">(PHONE RINGING)</font>

78
00:08:06,136 --> 00:08:07,464
Adele Delisi speaking.

79
00:08:07,489 --> 00:08:10,688
<i>Will you accept a collect
call from Jack Foley?</i>

80
00:08:11,808 --> 00:08:13,742
Yeah, I'll accept.

81
00:08:13,810 --> 00:08:16,836
- Hey, Adele, how you doin'?
- Hey, bank robber.

82
00:08:16,913 --> 00:08:21,509
Want some advice? Next time,
keep the engine running. <font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

83
00:08:21,585 --> 00:08:25,021
- Huh-huh. That's funny!
- What do you want, Jack?

84
00:08:25,088 --> 00:08:30,424
Adele, you know that Super Bowl party
that was for next Sunday?

85
00:08:30,494 --> 00:08:33,258
They changed the date.
It's tonight at 6:30.

86
00:08:33,330 --> 00:08:36,378
Didn't you tell me one
time calls aren't monitored?

87
00:08:36,403 --> 00:08:37,984
<i>I said, not as a rule.</i>

88
00:08:38,034 --> 00:08:40,696
So why don't you just come right out
and tell me what you're talkin' about?

89
00:08:40,771 --> 00:08:43,073
Listen to Miss Smarty Mouth,
out there in the free world.

90
00:08:43,098 --> 00:08:44,526
Oh, yeah, what's
free about it?

91
00:08:44,574 --> 00:08:46,667
I'm lookin' for work.

92
00:08:46,743 --> 00:08:51,612
- What about Mandrake the Magician?
- Emil, The Amazing, huh?

93
00:08:51,681 --> 00:08:55,742
He fired me.
Hired a younger girl... a redhead.

94
00:08:55,819 --> 00:08:58,982
Adele, the reason I'm calling...
they changed the date.

95
00:08:59,055 --> 00:09:02,684
It is tonight. It's 6:30.
That's like a few hours from now.

96
00:09:02,759 --> 00:09:03,363
You tell Buddy...

97
00:09:03,388 --> 00:09:05,411
Okay, all right, and the
guy driving the other car?

98
00:09:05,462 --> 00:09:06,884
What are you talking about?

99
00:09:06,909 --> 00:09:09,752
Well, seeing as you have
so much luck with cars,

100
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:12,530
Buddy thought it might be
better to bring two, you know?

101
00:09:12,602 --> 00:09:14,763
He got this guy who says
you know him, from Lompoc...

102
00:09:14,838 --> 00:09:17,568
- Uh, Glenn somebody...
- Glenn Michaels.

103
00:09:17,641 --> 00:09:21,509
Uh-huh, that's him. Buddy said
Glenn thinks you guys are real cool.

104
00:09:21,578 --> 00:09:23,512
- Adele?
- Yeah?

105
00:09:23,580 --> 00:09:27,914
You tell Buddy I see Glenn wearing
his sunglasses, I'm gonna step on 'em.

106
00:09:27,984 --> 00:09:31,147
- Might not even take 'em off first.
- Okay, honey. I'll do that.

107
00:09:31,221 --> 00:09:33,348
Now, you try not to get shot. Bye.

108
00:09:33,557 --> 00:09:35,491
Hey...

109
00:09:57,314 --> 00:09:59,782
Here, ma'am.
Let me help you with these.

110
00:09:59,850 --> 00:10:01,943
Beautiful young lady like you
shouldn't be carrying groceries.

111
00:10:02,018 --> 00:10:04,851
Let a man do that for you.
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font>

112
00:10:06,423 --> 00:10:11,122
Now, I didn't ask for your help,
so don't expect a tip.

113
00:10:11,194 --> 00:10:16,097
Oh, that's okay, ma'am.
I'll just take your car.

114
00:10:16,433 --> 00:10:18,401
Happy birthday.

115
00:10:18,468 --> 00:10:20,766
Did you fit another
Chanel suit in here?

116
00:10:20,837 --> 00:10:23,067
Something much better.
Go ahead, open it.

117
00:10:30,647 --> 00:10:33,912
Oh, my God.
It's beautiful.

118
00:10:33,984 --> 00:10:36,748
- It's a, um...
- Sig Sauer 380.

119
00:10:36,820 --> 00:10:41,723
- Right.
- Oh, I love it!

120
00:10:41,791 --> 00:10:43,725
Thanks, Dad.

121
00:10:43,793 --> 00:10:45,920
Happy birthday.

122
00:10:45,996 --> 00:10:47,964
- How 'bout some more coffee?
- You know, I can't.

123
00:10:48,031 --> 00:10:52,627
I have to go out to Glades, and then
I'm meeting Ray Nicolet at 10:00.

124
00:10:52,702 --> 00:10:55,296
Which one is that?
The A.T.F. Guy?

125
00:10:55,372 --> 00:10:58,933
Actually, he's with the F.B.I. Now.
He switched over.

126
00:10:59,009 --> 00:11:03,343
- He's still married, though.
- Technically. They're separated.

127
00:11:03,413 --> 00:11:05,847
- Well, so he's moved out then.
- He's about to.

128
00:11:05,916 --> 00:11:08,267
Well, then they're not
separated, are they?

129
00:11:08,292 --> 00:11:10,001
Can we not talk about this?

130
00:11:11,955 --> 00:11:13,368
What are you doing at Glades?

131
00:11:13,393 --> 00:11:15,779
Serving process... a
summons and complaint.

132
00:11:15,825 --> 00:11:18,817
Some con doing mandatory life
doesn't like macaroni and cheese.

133
00:11:18,895 --> 00:11:23,628
So, he files suit. Says he doesn't have
any choice in what they serve,

134
00:11:23,700 --> 00:11:26,134
and that violates
his civil rights.

135
00:11:26,202 --> 00:11:30,388
You can step in, work full-time
as one of my investigators.

136
00:11:30,413 --> 00:11:31,528
No, thanks.

137
00:11:31,575 --> 00:11:33,873
- You used to like it.
- <font color="#D900D9">(SCOFFS)</font> Dad.

138
00:11:33,944 --> 00:11:38,643
You'd meet doctors, lawyers... nothing
wrong with them, if they're divorced.

139
00:11:38,715 --> 00:11:43,414
Karen, why waste your time
on some cowboy cop...

140
00:11:43,486 --> 00:11:45,454
who drinks too much
and cheats on his wife?

141
00:11:45,522 --> 00:11:48,116
That's how those hot shots are...
all of 'em!

142
00:11:48,191 --> 00:11:50,125
I really gotta go.

143
00:11:53,997 --> 00:11:56,693
We don't talk much anymore.

144
00:11:56,766 --> 00:11:58,700
<font color="#D900D9">(KAREN SIGHS)</font>

145
00:11:58,768 --> 00:12:03,228
How 'bout I come over Sunday
and we watch the Super Bowl together?

146
00:12:03,306 --> 00:12:05,274
I'd like that.

147
00:12:06,343 --> 00:12:08,174
Thanks for the gun, Dad.

148
00:12:22,859 --> 00:12:25,453
They're right underneath you, Pup.
They dug a tunnel.

149
00:12:25,528 --> 00:12:31,160
I don't hear anything.
Where's the tunnel come out?

150
00:12:31,234 --> 00:12:34,067
Fourth post
from the guard tower.

151
00:12:34,137 --> 00:12:36,332
I don't see nothin'.

152
00:12:36,406 --> 00:12:38,340
You just keep watchin'.

153
00:12:56,159 --> 00:12:58,491
<font color="#D900D9">(PHONE SPEED-DIALING)</font>

154
00:12:58,561 --> 00:13:00,495
<font color="#D900D9">(LINE RINGS)</font>

155
00:13:00,563 --> 00:13:03,191
<i><font color="#808080">OPERATOR:</font> Federal Bureau of
Investigation, how may I direct your call?</i>

156
00:13:03,266 --> 00:13:05,791
Yeah, this is Karen Sisco again
for Ray Nicolet.

157
00:13:05,869 --> 00:13:07,962
Hold, please.

158
00:13:08,038 --> 00:13:09,972
Yeah.

159
00:13:28,525 --> 00:13:30,459
<font color="#D900D9">(SHUTS OFF ENGINE)</font>

160
00:13:30,527 --> 00:13:33,052
<i>The line is busy.
Would you like his voice mail?</i>

161
00:13:33,129 --> 00:13:36,394
No, forget it.
I'll call back later.

162
00:13:36,466 --> 00:13:38,400
- All right.
- Thanks.

163
00:13:39,703 --> 00:13:41,637
Still don't see anything.

164
00:13:43,840 --> 00:13:46,400
You will directly.

165
00:13:48,812 --> 00:13:51,337
<font color="#808080">PUP:</font>
Wait a minute.

166
00:14:11,935 --> 00:14:13,800
What the fuck?

167
00:14:20,744 --> 00:14:22,837
<font color="#D900D9">(HONKING HORN)</font>

168
00:14:28,618 --> 00:14:30,449
Two men by the fence!

169
00:14:33,189 --> 00:14:35,214
<font color="#D900D9">(MACHINE GUN FIRE)</font>

170
00:14:48,071 --> 00:14:50,403
What the hell is she doin'?

171
00:14:59,449 --> 00:15:02,043
Stop! Get your hands
in the air!

172
00:15:02,118 --> 00:15:04,313
<font color="#D900D9">(MACHINE GUN FIRE)</font>

173
00:15:06,723 --> 00:15:08,657
<font color="#D900D9">(MEN YELLING)</font>

174
00:15:19,135 --> 00:15:23,196
Tunnel's clear.
Seal up the north face.

175
00:15:23,273 --> 00:15:23,971
What happened?

176
00:15:23,996 --> 00:15:26,789
What the hell do you think, jackass?
Got a jail break!

177
00:15:26,843 --> 00:15:30,506
Cubans out in the cane. Don't point
that thing at me. Hey, Buddy.

178
00:15:30,580 --> 00:15:34,744
- It's okay, we're the good guys.
- What are you doing here?

179
00:15:34,818 --> 00:15:38,720
All right. You're just a girl. What do
you do for a living you pack a shotgun?

180
00:15:38,788 --> 00:15:41,559
I'm a federal marshal
and you're under arrest.

181
00:15:41,584 --> 00:15:43,647
That's probably all the hacks.

182
00:15:43,693 --> 00:15:46,059
Why don't we talk
about this later?

183
00:15:47,697 --> 00:15:49,631
Watch your head.

184
00:15:49,699 --> 00:15:51,530
I'm in. Let's go!

185
00:15:53,269 --> 00:15:57,103
- Hey! You comfy?
- If I could have a little more room...

186
00:15:57,173 --> 00:15:59,107
Well, there isn't any.

187
00:15:59,175 --> 00:16:02,201
We got a lot of shit in here.
We got handcuffs in here.

188
00:16:02,278 --> 00:16:04,872
What's in this can?

189
00:16:04,948 --> 00:16:07,883
That's for your breath. You could
use it... squirt some in your mouth.

190
00:16:07,951 --> 00:16:09,942
Yeah, well, that's mace, isn't it?

191
00:16:11,120 --> 00:16:13,816
<font color="#D900D9">(CAR STOPS)</font>

192
00:16:13,890 --> 00:16:16,586
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT VOICES)</font>

193
00:16:16,659 --> 00:16:19,685
All right, you! Get...

194
00:16:19,762 --> 00:16:21,696
<font color="#D900D9">(ENGINE ACCELERATES)</font>

195
00:16:21,764 --> 00:16:25,598
Hey. Where's your gun... pistol?

196
00:16:25,668 --> 00:16:28,728
In my bag, in the car.

197
00:16:39,148 --> 00:16:41,082
Boy, it stunk in there.

198
00:16:41,150 --> 00:16:44,916
I believe it. You're ruining
a $900 suit my dad gave me.

199
00:16:44,988 --> 00:16:47,548
Yeah, it went great
with that 12-gauge too.

200
00:16:47,624 --> 00:16:49,888
Why in the world would someone like you
become a federal marshal?

201
00:16:49,959 --> 00:16:52,038
The idea of going after
guys like you appealed to me.

202
00:16:52,063 --> 00:16:53,039
Sorry, what was that?

203
00:16:53,062 --> 00:16:55,189
Guys like me?
Let me tell you something.

204
00:16:55,265 --> 00:16:58,496
Even though I've been celibate lately,
I'm not going to force myself on you.

205
00:16:58,568 --> 00:17:01,249
- I've never done that in my life.
- You wouldn't have time, anyway.

206
00:17:01,271 --> 00:17:04,672
We come to a roadblock, they run the car
and find out who it belongs to.

207
00:17:04,741 --> 00:17:08,040
That's if they get set up in time,
which I doubt. If they do,

208
00:17:08,111 --> 00:17:12,104
they'll be lookin' for a bunch of little Latin
fellas, not a big black guy drivin' a Ford.

209
00:17:12,181 --> 00:17:15,309
He must be quite a pal,
to risk his own ass like this.

210
00:17:15,385 --> 00:17:17,410
Buddy? Yeah, he's a good guy.

211
00:17:17,487 --> 00:17:22,720
Back when we jailed together, he used to
call his sister every week, without fail.

212
00:17:22,792 --> 00:17:26,523
She's a born-again Christian. She does
bookkeeping for a televangelist.

213
00:17:26,596 --> 00:17:28,530
He'd call her up,
confess his sins.

214
00:17:28,598 --> 00:17:30,918
He'd tell her whatever bank
he happened to rob at the time.

215
00:17:30,934 --> 00:17:33,027
Buddy... that
his given name?

216
00:17:33,102 --> 00:17:35,536
The one I gave him, yeah.

217
00:17:35,605 --> 00:17:38,870
<font color="#808080">KAREN:</font>
So, what's your name?

218
00:17:38,942 --> 00:17:41,342
Be in the paper
tomorrow, anyway.

219
00:17:41,411 --> 00:17:44,642
Jack Foley.
You've probably heard of me.

220
00:17:44,714 --> 00:17:47,945
- Why? Are you famous?
- The time I was convicted in California,

221
00:17:48,017 --> 00:17:52,954
the F.B.I. Told me that I'd robbed
more banks than anybody in the computer.

222
00:17:53,022 --> 00:17:53,771
How many was that?

223
00:17:53,796 --> 00:17:55,708
Tell you the truth,
I don't really know.

224
00:17:55,758 --> 00:18:01,162
Started when I was 18 years old, driving
for my Uncle Cully, and his partner, Gus.

225
00:18:01,230 --> 00:18:05,826
So, basically you're saying
you spent half your life in prison.

226
00:18:05,902 --> 00:18:08,564
Basically, yeah.
I go back, I do 30 years. No time off.

227
00:18:08,638 --> 00:18:13,666
- You imagine lookin' at that?
- I don't have to. I don't rob banks.

228
00:18:16,312 --> 00:18:18,246
You don't seem all that scared.

229
00:18:18,314 --> 00:18:22,045
- Of course I am.
- You don't act like it.

230
00:18:22,118 --> 00:18:24,052
What do you want me
to do, scream?

231
00:18:24,120 --> 00:18:26,213
That wouldn't help much, anyway.

232
00:18:26,289 --> 00:18:31,955
No, I'm just gonna sit here, take it
easy, and wait for you to screw up.

233
00:18:32,028 --> 00:18:34,394
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>
You sound like my ex-wife.

234
00:18:34,464 --> 00:18:35,547
You were married?

235
00:18:35,572 --> 00:18:38,948
Just for about a year,
give or take a few days.

236
00:18:39,002 --> 00:18:41,869
It's not like we didn't get along...
we had fun. We just...

237
00:18:41,938 --> 00:18:45,533
didn't have... that thing,
you know, that uh...

238
00:18:45,608 --> 00:18:50,375
- That spark, you know? Gotta have that.
- Mm-hmm.

239
00:18:50,446 --> 00:18:52,744
- We still talk, though.
- Sure.

240
00:18:55,651 --> 00:18:58,245
This is not gonna end well.
These things never do.

241
00:18:58,321 --> 00:19:01,119
If it turns out I get shot
like a dog, it's gonna be in the street,

242
00:19:01,190 --> 00:19:03,249
not off a goddamn fence.

243
00:19:03,326 --> 00:19:06,989
You must really see yourself
as some kind of Clyde Barrow, huh?

244
00:19:11,567 --> 00:19:14,468
- You mean, of Bonnie and Clyde?
- Yeah.

245
00:19:18,174 --> 00:19:21,905
The part in the movie where they get
shot, when it's Warren Beatty and...

246
00:19:21,978 --> 00:19:24,503
- Faye Dunaway.
- Faye Dunaway, yeah.

247
00:19:24,580 --> 00:19:28,846
- I like her in that movie about TV.
- Network, yeah, she was good.

248
00:19:28,918 --> 00:19:32,012
And that guy says he's not gonna
take any more shit from anybody.

249
00:19:32,088 --> 00:19:34,682
- Peter Finch.
- Yeah! Peter Finch.

250
00:19:34,757 --> 00:19:38,784
"I'm mad as hell, and I'm not
gonna take any more of your shit!"

251
00:19:41,264 --> 00:19:43,596
In that part where they get shot,
I can remember thinkin' to myself,

252
00:19:43,666 --> 00:19:48,865
thinkin', "Hey, that wouldn't be
such a bad way to go, if you had to."

253
00:19:51,574 --> 00:19:53,508
<font color="#D900D9">(SIRENS)</font>

254
00:20:09,092 --> 00:20:11,026
You sure are easy to talk to.

255
00:20:15,098 --> 00:20:19,967
I was thinkin', if we met
under different circumstances...

256
00:20:20,036 --> 00:20:23,665
if you were in a bar and
I came up and we started talkin'...

257
00:20:23,739 --> 00:20:26,299
- I wonder what would happen.
- Nothing.

258
00:20:26,375 --> 00:20:29,503
- If you didn't know who I was.
- You'd probably tell me.

259
00:20:29,579 --> 00:20:31,600
Just saying if we met under
different circumstances...

260
00:20:31,625 --> 00:20:32,800
You have got to be kidding.

261
00:20:32,849 --> 00:20:35,818
Yeah. Yeah.

262
00:20:35,885 --> 00:20:40,754
Another movie I liked with Faye Dunaway
was Three Days of the Condor.

263
00:20:40,823 --> 00:20:43,485
The one with Robert Redford
when he was young.

264
00:20:43,559 --> 00:20:45,493
Yeah.

265
00:20:47,630 --> 00:20:50,793
You know, I never thought
it made sense, though...

266
00:20:50,867 --> 00:20:53,859
you know, the way
they got together so quick.

267
00:20:53,936 --> 00:20:55,870
Why not?

268
00:20:55,938 --> 00:20:58,202
- I mean, romantically.
- Mm-hmm.

269
00:21:01,244 --> 00:21:04,907
Well, but it... if... uh.
All right.

270
00:21:05,181 --> 00:21:08,048
Here we go. All right.
Where the hell are we?

271
00:21:08,117 --> 00:21:10,108
At the turnpike. Glenn's right above us
with the other car.

272
00:21:10,186 --> 00:21:13,178
- All right, c'mon. Hop on out.
- Turn around and get your hands up!

273
00:21:13,256 --> 00:21:15,315
- Shit!
- <font color="#D900D9">(GUNSHOTS)</font>

274
00:21:15,391 --> 00:21:17,621
We may as well leave her.
We're leavin' the car...

275
00:21:17,693 --> 00:21:19,456
and we gotta leave her someplace,
anyway... what's the difference where?

276
00:21:19,529 --> 00:21:20,399
She's comin' with us.

277
00:21:20,424 --> 00:21:22,454
Jesus Christ, what
were you doing in there?

278
00:21:22,498 --> 00:21:25,365
- Look for a name.
- I already looked.

279
00:21:25,434 --> 00:21:28,733
Her name is Karen Sisco. Like
the Cisco Kid, only spelled different.

280
00:21:28,804 --> 00:21:30,931
S-I-S-C-O.

281
00:21:31,007 --> 00:21:32,941
<font color="#D900D9">(SIRENS BLARING)</font>

282
00:21:35,578 --> 00:21:37,512
Karen?

283
00:21:37,580 --> 00:21:40,811
All right, Karen?
You be a good girl, now.

284
00:21:40,883 --> 00:21:42,908
- I'm gonna open up the trunk.
- <font color="#D900D9">(GUNSHOTS)</font>

285
00:21:42,985 --> 00:21:47,251
Hey, hey, hey, now!
Now, you're puttin' holes in your car!

286
00:21:47,323 --> 00:21:53,159
I'm not leavin' you. I'm gonna open the trunk
enough for you to drop your pistol out.

287
00:21:53,229 --> 00:21:56,858
Now, if you shoot, Buddy's got
your shotgun, he's gonna shoot back.

288
00:21:56,933 --> 00:21:59,800
There's nothin' I can do about it,
so it's up to you.

289
00:21:59,869 --> 00:22:04,806
Hey. Don't!
It's Glenn! Whoa!

290
00:22:04,874 --> 00:22:08,332
Fuck! Hey, hey, Jack.
Good to see you, man.

291
00:22:08,411 --> 00:22:11,778
What the fuck
are you guys shooting at?

292
00:22:11,847 --> 00:22:14,042
- Do we need 'im?
- The cop saw this car.

293
00:22:14,116 --> 00:22:16,355
He might tie it to the
break and turn around.

294
00:22:16,380 --> 00:22:17,109
All right.

295
00:22:17,153 --> 00:22:21,681
- Hey, Studs. We didn't recognize ya.
- Hey, "Studs," man.

296
00:22:21,757 --> 00:22:26,854
I haven't heard that since Lompoc, man.
So what's goin' on?

297
00:22:28,197 --> 00:22:30,131
Aw, nothin'.

298
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:35,193
Karen. Are you comin' out?

299
00:22:38,474 --> 00:22:41,204
- You hear that?
- Okay!

300
00:22:42,511 --> 00:22:44,445
Okay.

301
00:22:52,688 --> 00:22:54,622
You win, Jack.

302
00:23:05,501 --> 00:23:08,061
Now, you get your clothes cleaned,
you send me the bill.

303
00:23:08,137 --> 00:23:10,105
I'll send it to you at Glades.

304
00:23:10,172 --> 00:23:13,505
What, did you crawl through
a sewer, man? Who're you?

305
00:23:13,576 --> 00:23:16,977
- Take your sunglasses off.
- I see better with 'em on, man.

306
00:23:17,046 --> 00:23:19,310
You don't take 'em off I'm gonna throw
them off while they're still on your head.

307
00:23:19,382 --> 00:23:20,490
Go wait in the car.

308
00:23:20,515 --> 00:23:24,537
Um, we're in civilization now,
so you can ease up a little bit.

309
00:23:24,587 --> 00:23:28,819
I'm sorry. I'd like you to wait in the car,
please. Take her, put her in the back.

310
00:23:28,891 --> 00:23:32,827
- Okay. In the trunk?
- In the backseat! In the backseat!

311
00:23:32,895 --> 00:23:35,351
Backseat. Okay, you gotta come
now, 'cause I gotta do this...

312
00:23:35,376 --> 00:23:36,286
Gimme your jacket.

313
00:23:36,332 --> 00:23:38,698
Somebody forgot
to bring the clean clothes.

314
00:23:38,768 --> 00:23:40,827
I brought 'em. They're at Glades
in the back of the Cadillac.

315
00:23:40,903 --> 00:23:43,235
You decided to jump
into the trunk of her car.

316
00:23:43,306 --> 00:23:45,831
You can blame me if you want.
I don't mind.

317
00:23:45,908 --> 00:23:49,537
- Here, sir.
- I'll tell you...

318
00:23:49,612 --> 00:23:50,444
What's your problem, Jack?

319
00:23:50,469 --> 00:23:52,196
I don't know why you got
Glenn involved in this.

320
00:23:52,248 --> 00:23:54,114
How 'bout the score was
his idea to begin with?

321
00:23:54,139 --> 00:23:56,709
Idea... The guy's got a fuckin'
vacant lot for a head.

322
00:23:56,786 --> 00:24:00,722
He thinks he can talk
to me like that? Shit.

323
00:24:00,790 --> 00:24:05,727
"Gimme your jacket." I have been
sitting here for over a half-hour,

324
00:24:05,795 --> 00:24:09,595
watchin' out for the Highway Patrol,
if you think that's fun.

325
00:24:09,665 --> 00:24:13,123
God. You know, I hadda go
over there in the bushes...

326
00:24:13,202 --> 00:24:17,536
to smoke a joint, just so I could like,
<font color="#D900D9">(WHISTLES)</font> you know?

327
00:24:17,606 --> 00:24:22,407
Yep. I got somethin'
big lined up, up north.

328
00:24:22,478 --> 00:24:26,812
Yeah, these guys? Wouldn't even fuckin'
know about it if it wasn't for me.

329
00:24:26,882 --> 00:24:29,134
Every time he opens his
mouth, I wanna punch him out.

330
00:24:29,159 --> 00:24:30,364
He's not the problem, Jack.

331
00:24:30,419 --> 00:24:31,936
You wanna pull your head
outta your ass, tell

332
00:24:31,961 --> 00:24:33,412
me why the hell we're
bringing her with us?

333
00:24:33,456 --> 00:24:35,686
- Glenn.
- <font color="#D900D9">(MUMBLING)</font>

334
00:24:35,758 --> 00:24:38,056
You don't remember me, do you?

335
00:24:40,062 --> 00:24:42,377
Um, couldn't have been
Glades if that's what

336
00:24:42,402 --> 00:24:44,819
you're thinkin', 'cause
I was never out there.

337
00:24:44,867 --> 00:24:48,667
- No, that's not what I'm thinking.
- Oh, yeah?

338
00:24:48,738 --> 00:24:52,230
But you're sure
we've met, huh?

339
00:24:52,308 --> 00:24:54,003
- Last fall.
- <font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

340
00:24:54,076 --> 00:24:59,139
I drove you from the Palm Beach County
Jail to the federal courthouse... twice.

341
00:24:59,215 --> 00:25:01,547
You're Glenn Michaels.

342
00:25:01,617 --> 00:25:04,347
I never forget anybody
I've cuffed and shackled.

343
00:25:04,420 --> 00:25:07,116
Now let's think about this for a minute,
Glenn, see if we can't work it out.

344
00:25:07,189 --> 00:25:10,852
Do we have a gun in the car?

345
00:25:10,926 --> 00:25:13,759
Oh, shit!
I remember you! Hey!

346
00:25:13,829 --> 00:25:17,128
Foley's not gonna make it,
and if he goes down, you go with him.

347
00:25:17,199 --> 00:25:19,333
Now, look. I can understand
if you guys are close, but...

348
00:25:19,358 --> 00:25:20,056
No, we're not.

349
00:25:20,102 --> 00:25:25,335
- But, yeah. I'm helpin' him.
- Now wait a minute, Glenn.

350
00:25:25,408 --> 00:25:27,342
Have you helped him?

351
00:25:27,410 --> 00:25:31,574
I mean, technically, at this point, I doubt
you could be charged with aiding a fugitive.

352
00:25:31,647 --> 00:25:33,615
So you still have a choice.

353
00:25:33,682 --> 00:25:37,675
You wanna take her to my place, get
cleaned up, come out of the bathroom...

354
00:25:37,753 --> 00:25:40,847
with your aftershave on, and she goes,
"Oh. I had you all wrong."

355
00:25:40,923 --> 00:25:42,857
No. I just wanna talk
to her again, that's all.

356
00:25:42,925 --> 00:25:46,725
I just wanna see what it might have
been like under normal circumstances.

357
00:25:46,796 --> 00:25:49,230
- It's too late for that, Jack.
- <font color="#D900D9">(CAR ENGINE STARTING)</font>

358
00:25:49,298 --> 00:25:51,664
He wants to get out of here,
and I don't blame him.

359
00:26:11,220 --> 00:26:14,519
<font color="#D900D9">(CROWD CHEERING)</font>

360
00:26:30,473 --> 00:26:34,432
Ref don't call it soon, Snoop's gonna
send this cat out in a body bag.

361
00:26:35,911 --> 00:26:38,607
Anybody ever tell you
why they call him "Snoopy"?

362
00:26:40,816 --> 00:26:43,376
He used to be
Maurice "Mad Dog" Miller...

363
00:26:43,452 --> 00:26:45,920
back when he was a pro.

364
00:26:47,590 --> 00:26:49,558
Now you pet him,
he goes down.

365
00:26:55,798 --> 00:26:58,767
- I don't believe it!
- Oh, my!

366
00:26:58,834 --> 00:27:03,203
<font color="#D900D9">(CROWD CHATTERING, BOOING)</font>

367
00:27:03,272 --> 00:27:06,070
<font color="#D900D9">(CROWD CHANTING)</font>
Bullshit! Bullshit!

368
00:27:09,411 --> 00:27:11,572
Yeah, you the man.

369
00:27:16,952 --> 00:27:18,920
Guy's bragging he won
a thrown fight.

370
00:27:18,988 --> 00:27:20,922
Fuckin' pathetic.

371
00:27:24,760 --> 00:27:26,694
Dangerous is what it is.

372
00:27:30,366 --> 00:27:33,802
- Who's the bald dude?
- Richard Ripley.

373
00:27:33,869 --> 00:27:36,303
The Wall Street guy?

374
00:27:36,372 --> 00:27:39,102
Call him Dick The Ripper on account
of all the guys he ripped off.

375
00:27:39,174 --> 00:27:42,405
Oh, yeah. I didn't
recognize him without his rug.

376
00:27:42,478 --> 00:27:44,503
- What's his bid?
- Three years.

377
00:27:44,580 --> 00:27:47,640
You guys on the bench? Okay.

378
00:27:47,716 --> 00:27:51,777
Three years, fined $50 million
and wrote 'em a fuckin' check.

379
00:27:51,854 --> 00:27:53,822
Just like that.

380
00:27:53,889 --> 00:27:56,551
<font color="#D900D9">(STRAINING)</font>
Fifty mill, signed his name.

381
00:27:56,625 --> 00:27:59,719
Didn't even... Didn't even...
Okay, a little help.

382
00:27:59,795 --> 00:28:01,626
Okay, heavy!
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

383
00:28:01,697 --> 00:28:03,631
Heavy! Come on!

384
00:28:05,301 --> 00:28:07,235
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

385
00:28:07,303 --> 00:28:11,205
All the bright glare out here, you
couldn't read the numbers on the weights.

386
00:28:11,273 --> 00:28:14,140
Oh. I had it. Jesus.

387
00:28:14,209 --> 00:28:17,975
- How do you know he wrote a check?
- Uh, he told me.

388
00:28:18,047 --> 00:28:20,641
We work laundry together.

389
00:28:20,716 --> 00:28:22,980
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>
Guy loves to fucking talk.

390
00:28:23,052 --> 00:28:26,249
Yeah, he loves to talk.
He talked to the U.S. Attorney.

391
00:28:26,322 --> 00:28:28,847
Rolled over on all the snitches
he was doing business with.

392
00:28:28,924 --> 00:28:33,327
Hey! Any guy who can write
a fuckin' check for $50 million,

393
00:28:33,395 --> 00:28:36,990
he says anything,
I'm all fuckin' ears.

394
00:28:37,066 --> 00:28:41,002
Guy tells me he's got
all this money in foreign banks.

395
00:28:41,070 --> 00:28:43,470
Plus, around, mmm,

396
00:28:43,539 --> 00:28:47,407
five million in uncut diamonds
at his house.

397
00:28:47,476 --> 00:28:49,410
He said, quote,

398
00:28:49,478 --> 00:28:52,345
that I can get my hands on it
at any time.

399
00:28:52,414 --> 00:28:54,644
- Where does he live?
- Detroit.

400
00:28:54,717 --> 00:28:59,882
Snoopy Miller says that uncut diamonds
are as easy to move as cash.

401
00:29:02,391 --> 00:29:04,723
Ever seen
an uncut diamond, Studs?

402
00:29:04,793 --> 00:29:07,591
Looks just like
a plain, old rock.

403
00:29:07,663 --> 00:29:11,724
- Wait, you think this guy's lying?
- <font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLING)</font>

404
00:29:14,069 --> 00:29:17,436
What do you think, Studs? Use
your head. Some guy's got $5 million...

405
00:29:17,506 --> 00:29:22,136
socked away in his house, and he's gonna tell
some motormouth he just met in prison about it.

406
00:29:23,545 --> 00:29:26,070
Oh, I see.
You guys are cynical. Right.

407
00:29:37,026 --> 00:29:38,960
Here it comes.

408
00:29:52,608 --> 00:29:55,406
Keep on walking. Keep walking.

409
00:29:55,477 --> 00:29:57,877
You don't wanna be
answering any questions.

410
00:30:05,487 --> 00:30:07,785
I'm just saying
she wasn't scared, that's all.

411
00:30:07,856 --> 00:30:11,121
That's 'cause she had her hand on her gun
the whole time waitin' to make her move.

412
00:30:11,193 --> 00:30:14,026
You're just jealous 'cause
it was me in the trunk with her...

413
00:30:14,096 --> 00:30:16,030
- and not you.
- You're right.

414
00:30:16,098 --> 00:30:19,898
The first thing I'm gonna do...
is get this mud off me.

415
00:31:53,729 --> 00:31:55,754
Hey.

416
00:32:24,626 --> 00:32:26,719
<font color="#808080">MR. SISCO:</font>
Karen?

417
00:32:26,795 --> 00:32:27,921
Karen, honey?

418
00:32:29,198 --> 00:32:32,497
Karen?

419
00:32:32,568 --> 00:32:34,900
You were talking
in your sleep.

420
00:32:34,970 --> 00:32:36,904
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

421
00:32:39,775 --> 00:32:41,936
What'd I say?

422
00:32:42,010 --> 00:32:43,944
"Hey, yourself."

423
00:32:45,914 --> 00:32:48,906
- Huh.
- <font color="#D900D9">(KNOCK AT DOOR)</font>

424
00:32:48,984 --> 00:32:51,509
<font color="#808080">KAREN:</font>
Hello, Daniel.

425
00:32:54,823 --> 00:32:56,757
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font>

426
00:32:56,825 --> 00:33:01,262
Daniel Burdon, F.B.I.

427
00:33:01,330 --> 00:33:03,730
Marshall Sisco, Karen's dad.

428
00:33:03,799 --> 00:33:05,733
- Hmm.
- Hmm.

429
00:33:05,801 --> 00:33:07,735
Umm...

430
00:33:07,803 --> 00:33:10,931
Would you mind, please,
waiting outside?

431
00:33:11,006 --> 00:33:13,099
We have some business
to do here.

432
00:33:15,410 --> 00:33:17,776
Well, uh, I have
to use the john anyway.

433
00:33:17,846 --> 00:33:19,780
- Excuse me.
- Yeah.

434
00:33:24,686 --> 00:33:27,814
I wanna be
on the task force, Daniel.

435
00:33:27,890 --> 00:33:30,188
Well...

436
00:33:30,259 --> 00:33:34,753
That's nice of you
to offer, Karen, but...

437
00:33:34,830 --> 00:33:38,891
I got all the help
I can use right now.

438
00:33:38,967 --> 00:33:43,427
Instead, let's talk about
how you got that bump on your head.

439
00:33:43,505 --> 00:33:45,973
Isn't that my file
you're holding on to?

440
00:33:46,041 --> 00:33:49,238
Yes, but I want
to hear it from you,

441
00:33:49,311 --> 00:33:52,838
starting... with when
you grabbed the wheel.

442
00:33:52,915 --> 00:33:55,748
Where was this?

443
00:33:55,817 --> 00:33:57,751
Coming to the Okeechobee exit.

444
00:33:57,819 --> 00:34:00,982
