Nah, man,
it's my sister.

1101
01:12:17,984 --> 01:12:20,179
My sister believes
in fate but not hell.

1102
01:12:20,253 --> 01:12:22,373
That's why she stopped praying
for all the lost souls,

1103
01:12:22,388 --> 01:12:24,549
since you don't hear that much
about purgatory anymore.

1104
01:12:24,624 --> 01:12:27,991
But every day, she asks her boss
to pray that Buddy don't fuck up.

1105
01:12:28,061 --> 01:12:30,655
- <font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>
- I mean, what do you think?

1106
01:12:30,730 --> 01:12:33,198
- Well...
- You think there's a hell?

1107
01:12:33,266 --> 01:12:36,133
Yeah, it's called
the Glades Correctional Institute.

1108
01:12:36,202 --> 01:12:38,602
I'm sure as shit not going back there
or any place like it.

1109
01:12:38,671 --> 01:12:41,003
They put a gun on you,
you'll go, brother.

1110
01:12:42,709 --> 01:12:45,701
They put a gun on you,
you still have a choice.

1111
01:12:48,081 --> 01:12:52,074
So, Mr. Foley,

1112
01:12:52,151 --> 01:12:56,713
Mr. Ripley and I have had a long
discussion about your role in the company,

1113
01:12:56,789 --> 01:12:59,383
and it was his feeling you'd be
happiest working down here in Miami.

1114
01:12:59,459 --> 01:13:02,053
- How's that sound to you?
- Sounds great.

1115
01:13:02,128 --> 01:13:05,393
Good. You're about
a 42 long, right?

1116
01:13:07,800 --> 01:13:11,600
I uh, I'm about a 42...

1117
01:13:11,671 --> 01:13:13,605
like, 42 regular.

1118
01:13:21,614 --> 01:13:23,809
- Okay, let's see how she fits.
- What is that?

1119
01:13:23,883 --> 01:13:25,817
Your uniform.

1120
01:13:28,021 --> 01:13:29,955
My uniform.

1121
01:13:31,324 --> 01:13:33,315
Mr. Foley. Mr. Foley!

1122
01:13:34,494 --> 01:13:36,655
Sir, sir. Excuse me, sir.

1123
01:13:36,729 --> 01:13:39,095
Sir! Sir, excuse me!

1124
01:13:39,165 --> 01:13:39,786
You can't go in there!

1125
01:13:39,811 --> 01:13:41,248
Are you fucking kidding me?
A security guard?

1126
01:13:41,301 --> 01:13:43,895
- What are you, stoned?
- Hey, hey! Take it easy!

1127
01:13:43,970 --> 01:13:45,904
It's all right, Peggy.
It's under control.

1128
01:13:48,341 --> 01:13:50,571
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>
You know something?

1129
01:13:50,643 --> 01:13:53,612
I wasn't sure that you'd show up here,
but I was very sure if you did,

1130
01:13:53,680 --> 01:13:56,308
you'd throw this job
in my face.

1131
01:13:56,382 --> 01:13:58,316
Let me tell you
something.

1132
01:13:58,384 --> 01:14:01,842
Every single thing you've done
with your life up until this point...

1133
01:14:01,921 --> 01:14:04,355
in the real world
means nothing.

1134
01:14:04,424 --> 01:14:06,358
Less than nothing.

1135
01:14:06,426 --> 01:14:08,485
You're a bank robber.

1136
01:14:08,561 --> 01:14:11,291
That's not
a very marketable skill.

1137
01:14:11,364 --> 01:14:14,094
We don't see a lot
of old bank robbers walking around...

1138
01:14:14,167 --> 01:14:17,102
with a pension plan,
now do we?

1139
01:14:17,170 --> 01:14:19,138
I think you know this.
That's why you're here.

1140
01:14:19,205 --> 01:14:21,935
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>
Today, I've offered you...

1141
01:14:22,008 --> 01:14:25,273
a lousy job with a lousy wage.

1142
01:14:25,345 --> 01:14:29,441
You want something better?
Why don't you show me you can change?

1143
01:14:29,515 --> 01:14:32,712
Then I'll offer you
something better, a lot better.

1144
01:14:32,785 --> 01:14:36,277
But until then, my friend,
you'll have to earn it.

1145
01:14:37,690 --> 01:14:39,624
How, Dick?
The way you earn it?

1146
01:14:40,760 --> 01:14:42,785
Married some rich broad
owns the company,

1147
01:14:42,862 --> 01:14:44,902
selling it off a piece at a time
then divorcing her?

1148
01:14:44,964 --> 01:14:49,367
What's this Knute Rockne "pull yourself
up by the bootstraps" bullshit?

1149
01:14:49,435 --> 01:14:52,632
Back in prison, a guy like you
in a place like that?

1150
01:14:52,705 --> 01:14:56,004
You were ice cream for freaks.
A goddamned dumpling.

1151
01:14:56,075 --> 01:14:59,567
Maurice and a dozen other guys would
have bled you till you had nothing.

1152
01:14:59,645 --> 01:15:02,808
Until you were nothing.
I saved your ass!

1153
01:15:02,882 --> 01:15:05,373
So you'll pardon me if I don't want
to sit on a fucking stool all day,

1154
01:15:05,451 --> 01:15:08,648
and say, "Sign in here, please,"
or "Hey, pal, you can't park here."

1155
01:15:08,721 --> 01:15:11,884
All right, Dick?
I can't fuckin' do it, Dick!

1156
01:15:11,958 --> 01:15:13,926
- I'm disappointed in you.
- You wanna...

1157
01:15:13,993 --> 01:15:16,553
Oh, here we go.
What job did he promise you boys?

1158
01:15:16,629 --> 01:15:19,189
- There's two ways we can do this.
- Yeah, what are they?

1159
01:16:03,776 --> 01:16:07,906
Hey, Buddy, I gotta get a better pair
of shoes and some things for tomorrow.

1160
01:16:07,980 --> 01:16:09,914
Drop me off by the Ren Center
and we'll hook up later?

1161
01:16:09,982 --> 01:16:12,849
Yeah, okay.

1162
01:16:12,919 --> 01:16:14,580
I better go call my sister.

1163
01:16:17,857 --> 01:16:20,291
<font color="#D900D9">(SOFT JAZZ PIANO)</font>

1164
01:16:30,303 --> 01:16:32,897
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font>
Can I get you anything?

1165
01:16:32,972 --> 01:16:35,338
Yeah, I'll have a bourbon, please.
Water back.

1166
01:16:35,408 --> 01:16:37,342
Okay.

1167
01:16:39,779 --> 01:16:42,907
Hey, Tad, why don't
you do us again, please?

1168
01:16:42,982 --> 01:16:46,179
Oh, and, Celeste,
put the lady's drink on our bill.

1169
01:16:47,787 --> 01:16:49,948
<font color="#D900D9">(SOFT CHATTERING)</font>

1170
01:16:57,430 --> 01:17:00,661
- They want to buy your drink for you.
- Yeah, I get that.

1171
01:17:00,733 --> 01:17:03,099
- Tell them I'd rather pay for my own.
- Okay.

1172
01:17:07,874 --> 01:17:09,808
I'll find out.

1173
01:17:13,446 --> 01:17:15,437
Excuse me.

1174
01:17:15,515 --> 01:17:17,983
My associates and I,
we made a little bet...

1175
01:17:18,050 --> 01:17:20,018
