for a living.

1176
01:17:20,086 --> 01:17:23,055
And I won.
Hi, I'm Phillip.

1177
01:17:23,122 --> 01:17:26,819
If it's okay with you, Phillip, I'd
rather just have a quiet drink and leave.

1178
01:17:26,893 --> 01:17:30,795
Don't you want to know what I guessed?
How I know what you do for a living?

1179
01:17:30,863 --> 01:17:33,991
Really, Phillip, I don't want to be
rude. I just want to be left alone.

1180
01:17:40,573 --> 01:17:43,007
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>
It's a little cold over there.

1181
01:17:47,513 --> 01:17:49,447
<font color="#D900D9">(CLEARS THROAT)</font>

1182
01:17:49,515 --> 01:17:52,006
Excuse me.
I think I know why you're depressed.

1183
01:17:52,084 --> 01:17:55,315
If I can offer
my observation.

1184
01:17:56,489 --> 01:17:59,652
See, I got a hunch
you're the new sales rep,

1185
01:17:59,725 --> 01:18:04,924
and the client's not exactly knocked out
by the fact that a young lady...

1186
01:18:04,997 --> 01:18:09,263
even one as stunning as yourself...
is handling the account.

1187
01:18:09,335 --> 01:18:12,236
Am I close?
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

1188
01:18:12,305 --> 01:18:14,239
I'm Andy.

1189
01:18:15,975 --> 01:18:21,572
We're all ad guys. Flew in this morning
from the apple... New York.

1190
01:18:21,647 --> 01:18:24,445
Came in to pitch
Hiram Walker Distillery.

1191
01:18:24,517 --> 01:18:27,543
Little test market campaign
for the new margarita mix.

1192
01:18:27,620 --> 01:18:31,750
It's really pretty interesting.
We take this, um,

1193
01:18:31,824 --> 01:18:34,384
Mex... um,
Hispanic bandito...

1194
01:18:34,460 --> 01:18:38,021
with his bullet belts and everything,
and the big Chihuahua hat,

1195
01:18:38,097 --> 01:18:40,895
and he pulls out
his six-guns,

1196
