There's only one waitress.

1206
01:19:47,504 --> 01:19:48,356
I can go to the bar.

1207
01:19:48,401 --> 01:19:50,767
- Oh, don't go.
- Are those guys bothering you?

1208
01:19:50,836 --> 01:19:52,804
No, they're fine.
I mean, you just got here.

1209
01:19:57,276 --> 01:19:59,210
Here, help yourself.

1210
01:20:01,113 --> 01:20:03,638
- You like bourbon?
- I love it.

1211
01:20:03,716 --> 01:20:07,152
We got that out of the way. Tell me,
Celeste, what do you do for a living?

1212
01:20:07,219 --> 01:20:10,814
I'm a sales rep,
and I came here to call on a customer,

1213
01:20:10,890 --> 01:20:13,017
but they gave me a hard time
'cause I'm a girl.

1214
01:20:13,092 --> 01:20:15,026
Is that how
you think of yourself?

1215
01:20:15,094 --> 01:20:17,028
- As a sales rep?
- As a girl.

1216
01:20:17,096 --> 01:20:19,087
- Yeah, I don't have a problem with it.
- I like your hair.

1217
01:20:19,165 --> 01:20:20,255
I like your outfit.

1218
01:20:20,280 --> 01:20:23,148
Actually, this is my
second favorite outfit.

1219
01:20:23,202 --> 01:20:26,535
I had a first favorite, but it got
ruined and I had to get rid of it.

1220
01:20:26,605 --> 01:20:28,539
- You did?
- It smelled.

1221
01:20:28,607 --> 01:20:31,132
- Really? Having it cleaned didn't help?
- No.

1222
01:20:31,210 --> 01:20:33,144
So tell me, Gary,
what do you do for a living?

1223
01:20:33,212 --> 01:20:36,204
- How far do you want to go with this?
- Don't say anything yet.

1224
01:20:36,282 --> 01:20:38,682
I don't think it works
if we're somebody else.

1225
01:20:38,751 --> 01:20:40,685
I mean, Gary and Celeste,
what do they know about anything?

1226
01:20:40,753 --> 01:20:42,566
Well, this is your game,
I've never played before.

1227
01:20:42,591 --> 01:20:43,337
It's not a game.

1228
01:20:43,389 --> 01:20:45,550
It's not something you play.

1229
01:20:45,624 --> 01:20:47,615
Well, does this make
any sense to you?

1230
01:20:47,693 --> 01:20:50,025
It doesn't have to.
It's something that happens.

1231
01:20:50,096 --> 01:20:55,159
It's like seeing someone for the first time...
like you could be passing on the street,

1232
01:20:55,234 --> 01:20:58,499
and you look at each other
and for a few seconds...

1233
01:20:58,571 --> 01:21:02,007
there's this kind of a recognition...
like you both know something.

1234
01:21:02,074 --> 01:21:04,941
The next moment,
the person's gone,

1235
01:21:05,010 --> 01:21:08,411
and it's too late
to do anything about it.

1236
01:21:08,481 --> 01:21:11,314
And you always remember it,
because it was there, and you let it go,

1237
01:21:11,383 --> 01:21:14,750
and you think to yourself, "What if I
had stopped? If I had said something?"

1238
01:21:14,820 --> 01:21:16,754
"What if?"

1239
01:21:16,822 --> 01:21:18,790
"What if?"

1240
01:21:18,858 --> 01:21:22,919
And it may only happen
a few times in your life.

1241
01:21:25,164 --> 01:21:28,565
- Or once.
- Or once.

1242
01:22:04,703 --> 01:22:07,263
<font color="#808080">KAREN:</font>
How'd you find me?

1243
01:22:07,339 --> 01:22:09,273
Uh...

1244
01:22:11,043 --> 01:22:13,341
Called your room
from downstairs.

1245
01:22:13,412 --> 01:22:15,846
Oh.
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

1246
01:22:17,183 --> 01:22:19,174
And if I had answered,
what were you gonna say?

1247
01:22:19,251 --> 01:22:23,620
I would say who I was, and do you remember
me, and want to meet for a drink?

1248
01:22:23,689 --> 01:22:28,626
If I remembered you.
I came here looking for you.

1249
01:22:28,694 --> 01:22:31,458
All right, so then I would have
said yes, but for all you know,

1250
01:22:31,530 --> 01:22:33,964
I could have had a SWAT team waiting
for you... why would you trust me?

1251
01:22:34,033 --> 01:22:36,024
It'd be worth the risk.

1252
01:22:36,101 --> 01:22:38,626
- You like taking risks.
- So do you.

1253
01:22:40,940 --> 01:22:43,272
<font color="#808080">KAREN:</font>
You know, sooner or later...

1254
01:22:46,846 --> 01:22:50,179
You really wear that suit.

1255
01:22:50,249 --> 01:22:52,809
Well, that's not
what you were about to say.

1256
01:22:52,885 --> 01:22:55,186
Remember how talkative
you were in the trunk?

1257
01:22:55,211 --> 01:22:55,810
Mm-hmm.

1258
01:22:55,855 --> 01:22:57,657
Adele said you do that
when you're nervous.

1259
01:22:57,682 --> 01:22:58,746
Oh, she did, did she?

1260
01:23:00,259 --> 01:23:04,355
- You kept touching me, feeling my thigh.
- But in a nice way.

1261
